post_text:
SPORTS UPDATE: FamilyID registration will open for the High School Low Risk Sports of Boys & Girls Soccer, Cross Country, and Girls Tennis on Monday, September 14. Any high school students interested in participating in these sports should go to the district homepage www.portchesterschools.org to register. Practices will begin on September 29th.

The NYS Department of Health classified High Risk Sports of Football, Volleyball, and Cheerleading have been moved to a March 1, 2021 start date.

Girls Swimming and all modified (Middle School) sports are currently on hold until a decision is made by our local governing body (Section 1) on their status.

post_text: This summer, the Port Chester School District will run an optional distance learning summer program for incoming grades 1-5 students to practice their ELA and math skills. We anticipate the virtual program to run during the month of July, Monday through Thursday from 9 am to 11 am. If you are interested in having your child participate, please fill out this form no later than Monday, June 15th at 9 am. Visit our website for more information and to fill out a form for your child's specific school.

post_text: This is an important budget/board election vote update from the Port Chester Public Schools. The opening and counting of absentee ballots will now be live- streamed beginning 5 pm, Tuesday June 16, not June 9 as originally scheduled. This morning, Governor Cuomo issued Executive Order 202.39 extending the deadline until June 16, 2020 at 5 PM for the receipt of mailed absentee ballots. The deadline for submitting hand delivered ballots to the District Clerk or into the ballot drop box at 113 Bowman Ave. remains June 9, 2020 at 5 PM.
text: This is an important budget/board election vote update from the Port Chester Public Schools. The opening and counting of absentee ballots will now be live- streamed beginning 5 pm, Tuesday June 16, not June 9 as originally scheduled. This morning, Governor Cuomo issued Executive Order 202.39 extending the deadline until June 16, 2020 at 5 PM for the receipt of mailed absentee ballots. The deadline for submitting hand delivered ballots to the District Clerk or into the ballot drop box at 113 Bowman Ave. remains June 9, 2020 at 5 PM.

post_text:
We are pleased to invite you to participate in the planning process for re-opening Port Chester schools this fall. We are organizing a Back-to-School Task Force with different working groups and subgroups in order to begin these important conversations with stakeholders: parents, village leadership, community partners, older students, and educators. These working groups are generally organized into subgroups at each level: elementary, middle, and high school. Participants will need to commit to several one-two hour planning sessions to be scheduled in June in the coming weeks. The planning sessions will be live and online. The first meeting is Monday, June 8 at 4:00 p.m. If you wish to participate, information about how to join will be sent before the 8th and after you complete the interest survey.
If you are interested in serving on one of these groups/subgroups, then please respond to this interest survey (https://forms.gle/yJNDcSKRshZX7vPj9) with the requested information. For more information, please see the Overview document attached.

This is an important reminder from the Port Chester Public Schools to exercise your right to vote and complete and submit your ballot for the budget and board member election on June 9. Ballots must be received in the Board Offices at 113 Bowman Ave. by 5 pm, June 9 so allow enough time for mail delivery or drop your ballot off at the Board Offices from 8:30 am until 3:30 pm Monday through Friday or until 5 pm on June 9.

Este es un mensaje importante de las Escuelas Públicas de Port Chester. Recuerde ejercer su derecho de votar, completar y enviar su boleta para la elección del presupuesto y miembros de la junta de educación el 9 de junio. Las boletas deben recibirse en las oficinas de la Junta de Educación en 113 Bowman Ave. antes de las 5 pm, el 9 de junio. Por favor reserve suficiente tiempo para la entrega del correo o déjelo en las Oficinas de la Junta de 8:30 a.m. a 3:30 p.m. de lunes a viernes, o hasta las 5 p.m. el 9 de junio.

post_text: The Lower Hudson Regional Information Center has partnered with the Port Chester-Rye Union Free School District to provide technical support to students on district owned devices while remote learning is occurring. Support is available from 7 p.m. until 5 p.m. Monday through Friday. Please have a parent fill out the form (at https://lhric.service-now.com/student) to request assistance and provide us with the information needed for our technician to work with you on the issue. The technician will use the Parent/Guardian's email to communicate and in some cases may need to call to schedule a support session.

post_text:
Coronavirus Update - JFK Early Dismissal - March 6, 2020

Out of an abundance of caution, John F. Kennedy Elementary School students and staff were dismissed early today, March 6, 2020. Two children came to JFK Elementary School, and it was reported that one of their family members may have been in close proximity to someone with the novel coronavirus (COVID-19). The parents and children reported no symptoms.

The Westchester County Department of Health was contacted. An early dismissal was initiated so that the buildings could be properly sanitized. Parents were advised not to send children to school with flu symptoms or if they have been in close proximity to someone who may have been exposed to the novel coronavirus (COVID-19). An update will be provided to the community in a timely manner.

Out of an abundance of caution, John F. Kennedy Elementary School students and staff were dismissed early today, March 6, 2020. The parents and children reported no symptoms.

The Westchester County Department of Health was contacted. An early dismissal was initiated so that the buildings could be properly sanitized. Parents were advised not to send children to school with flu symptoms or if they have been in close proximity to someone who may have been exposed to the novel coronavirus (COVID-19). An update will be provided to the community in a timely manner.

post_text:
ANNOUNCEMENT
After a thorough, three-month process that involved constituent groups from the school, district, and community, the Port Chester Board of Education at its meeting on Feb. 6, 2020, appointed Mr. Luke Sotherden the next Principal of Port Chester High School effective July 1, 2020. Mr. Sotherden will become the 14th Principal of Port Chester High School.

Serving as an Assistant Principal at the high school for just over nine years, Mr. Sotherden emerged from a competitive field of 30 candidates and will provide a valued sense of continuity and consistency because of his experience and knowledge of Port Chester High School, its staff, families and the community. Throughout this process, Mr. Sotherden spoke of his love for the high school, the importance of the sense of "family" that he wants to continue to build here and his vision for making the school a place where all that is done continues to have meaning and purpose. In the next few months, Mr. Sotherden will work closely with current High School Principal, Dr. Combs, to ensure a smooth transition.
text:
ANNOUNCEMENT
After a thorough, three-month process that involved constituent groups from the school, district, and community, the Port Chester Board of Education at its meeting on Feb. 6, 2020, appointed Mr. Luke Sotherden the next Principal of Port Chester High School effective July 1, 2020. Mr. Sotherden will become the 14th Principal of Port Chester High School.

Serving as an Assistant Principal at the high school for just over nine years, Mr. Sotherden emerged from a competitive field of 30 candidates and will provide a valued sense of continuity and consistency because of his experience and knowledge of Port Chester High School, its staff, families and the community. Throughout this process, Mr. Sotherden spoke of his love for the high school, the importance of the sense of "family" that he wants to continue to build here and his vision for making the school a place where all that is done continues to have meaning and purpose. In the next few months, Mr. Sotherden will work closely with current High School Principal, Dr. Combs, to ensure a smooth transition.
